Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: YAML parsing errors

Solution: Validate YAML syntax using yamllint or online validators
Check indentation (use spaces, not tabs)
Issue: Permission denied errors

Solution: Ensure scripts have execute permissions: chmod +x script.py
Check file ownership and directory permissions
Issue: Import errors in Python scripts

Solution: Verify Python path includes necessary directories
Install required packages: pip install pyyaml
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated critical security vulnerabilities in GitHub Actions workflows and CI/CD pipelines. You learned how malicious actors can poison workflows to gain unauthorized access, extract secrets, and compromise build environments.

Key Takeaways:

Always validate workflow permissions and triggers
Implement least privilege access controls
Monitor workflow executions for anomalies
Use secret scanning and validation tools
Pin action versions to prevent supply chain attacks
Never expose secrets in logs or outputs
